 * Returns the byte at index |k| of |bytevector| as an exact integer in the
 * range [0..255]. It is an error if |k| is not a valid index of |bytevector|.
 *
 * @lisp
 * (bytevector-u8-ref ’#u8(1 1 2 3 5 8 13 21) 5    => 8
 * @end lisp
doc>
